// Class.dat
//
// This datafile contains definitions of all of the 
// Character Classes this game has.  A character must have a class.
//
// This data gets parsed into the master_class[] array, defined in data.vc
// The maximum number of items is controlled by MAX_CLASSES, defined in data.vc
//    please change this number of you wish to add more items than it currently 
//    allows.
//
// blank lines and commented lines are ignored.  Anything else will be treated as an entry.
//
// Entries go as follows:
//
// class_name	"class_description"
// skill_type, skill_type, skill_type, skill_type
//
// skill_group must reference entries by name in skilltypes.dat  
// A class may have any number of skillgroups up to MAX_SKILLGROUPS_PER_CLASS, which is 
//   defined in data.vc
// the skillgroups must be separated by commas.  Whitespace is optional.
//
// If a class has no skills, please put the NO_SKILLS token on the entry's second line.
//

